This is something that just really depends on tone. Everything can work, and even the best ideas-in-theory can be fucked over by bad execution.

>Operators from around the world attempt to stop an interdimensional threat, they have one chance.
Stands or falls with good, or at least believable, knowledge of military stuff. Not to mention the number of stories in this category that end up being tensionless power fantasies.

>one of the last habitable areas on the planet send a group out to sea in the search for much needed supplies, none have returned before them.
It's a well-trodden stereotype. Nothing really wrong with that. But just the description doesn't really spur the imagination.

>an AI awakens members of its cargo to fight a threat it is unable to overcome, the organic casualties considered acceptable in overcoming this obstacle are without limitations.
This seems to be the one with the most leeway. As in, what kind of ship are they on, what's the mission, how many people are there, what's the disposition of the AI, etc. etc.
